Children: --------- - property: (optional, qty: 0 or more) - allele-assignment: (not required, qty: 0 or more) Also known as interpretation. - typing-method: (required, qty: 1 or more) The 'typing-method' element encapsulates methods such as sso, ssp, sbt-sanger, and sbt-ngs. - consensus-sequence: (optional, qty: 0 to many) Consensus data for the results reported under typing-method. Also allows an optional "property" element that may have nested/custom use data related to the interpretation. Attributes: ----------- - gene-family: Represents the gene evaluated in this typing report, e.g. "HLA" or "KIR" (required) See: http://www.genenames.org/genefamilies for examples. - date: Typing/testing date for this sample (required)
